   {:e #blake3 "3ae2567bb381a338890a83ce0e81284a9e8865678bee229a719f56cdd330d6a7" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :runtime/req-54b178ca316db706; Session entity: :recon/trace-c603512ec7b1aed3; Session entity: :recon/trace-931698ac5681425e; Session entity: :recon/trace-77b704e9f550507c; Session entity: :recon/trace-d34d25315d48d672; Session entity: :recon/trace-c12d700371362cc1; Session entity: :task/t-c71c7410\nSession entity: :task/t-4e7c2524; Session entity: :task/t-fa7eb30a; C9-REDESIGN: Critical self-critique and architectural revision. FIVE PROBLEMS WITH CURRENT PLAN: (1) Corroboration formula is naive — distinct_agents/total_agents is a frequency ratio, not a Bayesian posterior. Need beta-binomial model where P(real finding | k of n agents report it) accounts for base rate of false positives. (2) Concept clustering is a known blocker — HashEmbedder concept-collapse (AUDIT-EXT) produces mega-clusters. Running corroboration on collapsed clusters is meaningless. C9-1 depends on functioning clustering which is currently broken. MITIGATION: operate at OBSERVATION level not CONCEPT level. Group observations by textual similarity of titles (cheap substring matching) rather than embeddings. (3) Regex dependency extraction is fragile — finding IDs like F-INV-001 are section headers in markdown, not datom entities. Entity resolution will fail for most references. MITIGATION: link to OBSERVATIONS (which ARE entities) not to audit document sections. Use the existing :exploration/mentions-entity attribute. (4) Only C9-5 (stagnation) is truly independent and immediately useful — it uses clean numerical data (load_trajectory), no embedding quality issues. Should be first priority. (5) User wants unix-style composable primitives, not monolithic seed integration. Current plan embeds synthesis INTO the seed pipeline. Better: build primitives that an agent can compose. The synthesis emerges from composition. REVISED APPROACH: Instead of 5 tightly coupled components, build 3 independent composable primitives plus 1 integration: PRIMITIVE-1 (independent): Stagnation detection — detect_stagnation(store) returns signal. Wire into methodology_gaps. Zero coupling to concept engine. PRIMITIVE-2 (independent): Agent provenance query — for any set of entities, group by creating agent and compute agreement metrics. Pure function over datoms, no concept dependency. PRIMITIVE-3 (independent): Observation graph builder — extract cross-references from observation bodies into :exploration/depends-on links. Uses entity_auto_link pattern. INTEGRATION: Seed corroboration boost — if primitives 1-3 exist, seed assembly can optionally use them. But each primitive is useful standalone via braid query.; Session entity: :task/t-5dcc97ae; Session entity: :task/t-7f200105" :op :assert}
